social_posts.post_text: Some of the last images of my time with the Summers family. I’ll be sharing part one later but for now part two. Shooting through anything is my favorite but add some beautiful white cosmos and soft light from a cloudy day and my heart was singing.

Logan and Austin wanted to move through their day and feel plus experience every minute of it. It was effortless and fluid. They tasted the hors d'oeuvres, hugged their people, danced, mingled and felt it all. Such an incredible day to watch unfold.
Just want to live In the warmth, love, and joy of a quiet tent full of people coming together for the celebration of two souls while words of admiration are being spoken. It’s something to drink up.
One of the last images I took of these two before they walked into a bustling reception. This moment will forever be a favorite of mine from 2022. So appropriately inappropriate.

How’s everyone holding up this week? Still celebrating or resting and ready for routine again? I think maybe I’m a little of both. 

So grateful for this time with family and for the year we are wrapping up. I’m almost completely full for next year and humbled by you and that realization. What an amazing thing we get to do together.

Finishing up the year with a grateful heart. Very grateful. 2022 was so incredible. Thank you for allowing me into some of the most memorable days of your lives, for being vulnerable in front of my camera, for trusting my art, for welcoming me like family. I have loved every minute. This life goes so fast. Being a mom and watching my babies get older makes me even more grateful for this job and these memories/gifts I am creating. This, you, life, memories, family. It is everything. 2022 you will be remembered fondly.

I am a documentary photographer by nature. I pride myself in moving through your day and letting it flow with ease and grace. Above everything I want you to enjoy your day and photography is just an after thought. But when the light hits like this I will absolutely stop everything and ask you to take a quick portrait. Nina and Rob were ready at this point of the day to retreat inside and take a quiet minute with each other before joining cocktail hour. I begged them to take 5 more minutes and stand in this light. Don’t kill me I thought. They didn’t. And the last pic in this series is them finally getting their quiet moment.

This is my group hug, my big I love you, my I couldn’t of done this without the support of every vendor, client, friend and family member that has and still pours into me. For 13 years I have built a business alongside some of the greatest souls I have ever met. Your trust and support has gotten me to this place of growth and grace. 

Next Tuesday I will officially launch my new brand. @lettersouth and her team have been working on this for almost a year. This is an identity worthy of my work - something I hope you will both see and feel. Scroll to see a little of what is to come. And a small representation of the many faces that have trusted me with their legacy. Along with the trust, I am handed an amount of love that I carry with me and into my family and all of my relationships. So for that WE thank you. Every. Singe. One of you.

New brand. New identity. Same girl. Same work in progress. Constantly growing. Forever grateful. Mark those calendars. 9.5.23

It’s live. My new site and branding. A new home for my work. A place I am excited to take up space in.

Biggest thanks to Janet over at @lettersouth for being not only my designer but becoming my friend and encourager in the process. 

New headshots from my girl @nataliewatson and a fun weekend in Nashville. And some much needed business coaching from Natalie with @ingoodcompanypr . 

Headed into my fall season with a big heart and lots excitement. Thanks for being here friends.
